Enum BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Timing

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Timing>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Timing>
    Enclosing interface:
    BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener

    public static enum BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Timing
extends java.lang.Enum<BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Timing>
    For BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Status.NATIVE_CONNECTION_FAILED, BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Status.DISCOVERING_SERVICES_FAILED, and BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Status.BONDING_FAILED, gives further timing information on when the failure took place. For all other reasons, BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.ConnectionFailEvent.timing() will be NOT_APPLICABLE.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      EVENTUALLY
      The operation failed in the native stack.
      IMMEDIATELY
      The operation failed immediately, for example by the native stack method returning false from a method call.
      NOT_APPLICABLE
      For reasons like BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Status.BLE_TURNING_OFF, BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Status.AUTHENTICATION_FAILED, etc.
      TIMED_OUT
      The operation took longer than the time dictated by BleNodeConfig.taskTimeoutRequestFilter.
